itter, and under logs, but sometimes it climbs on low bushes. It builds nests of leaves in rock crevices, burrows, and hollows among roots of trees. It does not hibernate.",,Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. The Shorttailed Gymnure has a wide distribution and relatively stable overall population.,Beer (2003) | Chernova et al. (2015) | Hutterer (2005a) | Jenkins & Robinson (2002) | Lekagul & McNeely (1988) | Medway (1983) | Nowak (1999) | Phillipps & Phillipps (2016) | Rudd (1980) | Ruedi et al. (1994) | Smith & Yan Xie (2013) | Sody (1933) | Stone (1995b) | Wu Delin et al. (1996),
