casions) returned to rest sites used the previous day.",,"Classified as Least Concern in The IUCN Red List. Very little is known about Small-toothed Ferret-badgers and more field studies are needed to learn more about their natural history, ecology, and conservation status. In Laos and Vietnam , there is often some confusion between Small-toothed and Large-toothed Ferret Badgers, so careful distinction between these two species needs to be made in these two countries. Small-toothed Ferret-badgers are hunted for their fur and meat in China and north-east India ; in China , their fur is used for collars and jackets.",Allen (1929) | Francis (2008) | Lekagul & McNeely (1991) | Neal (1986) | Storz & Wozencraft (1999) | Wang & Fuller (2003a) | Wozencraft (2005 | 2008) | Zhou et al. (2008),
