anthropogenic changes than most species of Nesomyinae . It has been previously considered the most common native rodent in western Madagascar, but in certain areas,this is not the case. It has been proposed that introduced House Mice ( Mus musculus) compete with Bastard’s Big-footed Mouse for burrows.",Carleton & Goodman (2003c) | Carleton & Schmidt (1990) | Dollar et al. (2007) | Ellerman (1949) | Ganzhorn et al. (1996) | Goodman & Griffiths (2009) | Goodman | Ganzhorn & Rakotondravony (2003) | Goodman | Mittermeier et al. (2014) | Goodman | Soarimalala et al. (2013) | Hawkins & Racey (2008) | Jansa et al. (2008) | Petter (1972a) | Petter & Randrianasolo (1961) | Rasoma & Goodman (2007) | Soarimalala & Goodman (2011),
