lined to enter torpor than females. Burrows provide thermal protection.",,Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List.,Corti et al. (2004) | Ellison (1993 | 1996) | Ellison & Skinner (1992) | Ellison | Bronner & Taylor (1993) | Ellison | Taylor et al. (1993) | Fitzherbert et al. (2007) | Gordon (1986) | Gordon & Rautenbach (1980) | Gordon & Watson (1986) | Hanney (1965) | Hickman & Machiné (1986) | Hurst | McCleery | Collier | Fletcher et al. (2013) | Hurst | McCleery | Collier | Silvy et al. (2014) | Kerley (1989) | Lovegrove & Raman (1998) | MacFadyen et al. (2012) | Maputla etal. (2011) | Mikula et al. (2016) | Monadjem (1997b | 1999a) | Monadjem et al. (2015) | Mzilikazi & Lovegrove (2002) | Perrin (2013a) | Perrin & Kokkinn (1986) | Petter (1966a) | Rautenbach (1982) | Smithers (1971) | Smithers & Tello (1976) | Smithers & Wilson (1979) | Speakman et al. (1994) | Westlin-van Aarde (1988 | 1989) | Yarnell et al. (2007),
