 reduced population. Due to its acute sense of smell and high level of intelligence,it has been trained to detect land mines.",Ajayi (1975) | Ansell & Dowsett (1988) | Ewer (1967) | Genest-Villard (1967) | Knight (1984) | Knight & Knight-Eloff (1987) | Monadjem et al. (2015) | Morris (1963) | Olayemi et al. (2012) | Perrin & Kokkinn (1986) | Poling et al. (2010) | Ray & Duplantier (2013) | Skinner & Chimimba (2005) | Smithers &Tello (1976) | Smithers & Wilson (1979),
