ulation trends of Rio de Janeiro Spiny-rats are unknown, butit is regarded as locally common. A primary major threat would be continued deforestation, but Rio de Janeiro Spinyrats occur in several municipal, state, and federal reserves.",Allen (1899a) | Davis (1945a | 1945b | 1947) | Glinther (1877a) | Lara et al. (1996) | Mello et al. (2015) | Moojen (1948) | Pessoa | Tavares | de Oliveira & Patton (2015),https://zenodo.org/record/6623697/files/figure.png
