itional studies on distribution, habitat, abundance, ecology, and conservation threats to Short-tailed Spiny-rat are needed.",Allen (1902) | Eisenberg & Redford (1999) | Emmons (1990 | 1997a) | Gunther (1877a) | Osgood (1944) | Patton (1987) | Patton & Gardner (1972) | Patton & Leite (2015) | Patton & Reig (1989) | Thomas (19014 | 1911b) | Woods & Kilpatrick (2005),https://zenodo.org/record/6623772/files/figure.png
