ctivity has been observed throughout the hours of darkness and at dawn concluding at c.06:00 h. Echolocation search calls consist of pulse sequences, with first harmonic peaking at frequencies of 39-2-41 • 1 kHz. These calls have narrow bandwidth and short durations (1-4-3 milliseconds). Search calls allow targeting of aerial prey from relatively long distances.",,,Ball (2004) | Bambini et al. (2006) | Burgess & Lee (2004) | Gerlach (2004 | 2009) | Gerlach & Taylor (2006) | Goodman | Puechmaille et al. (2012) | Hill (1956 | 1971a) | Joubert (2004) | Monadjem | Gerlach et al. (2017) | Nicoll & Suttie (1982) | NPTS (2003) | Rocamora & Joubert (2004) | Wright (1868),https://zenodo.org/record/3747956/files/figure.png
