o forage shortly before sunset in open forest habitats. Greatest energy of echolocation call is 45 kHz in second harmonic; call initially rises very slighdy and has downward sweep at its termination.,,"Classified as Least Concern on The IUCN Red List. Seri’s Sheath-tailed Bat has a large distribution, but its population is likely decreasing due to loss of forest habitat, forest fragmentation, and cave disturbance on the several islands in its distribution where human populations are rapidly increasing.",Bonaccorso (1998) | Colgan & Soheili (2008) | Flannery (1994 | 1995b) | Helgen (2008 a ) | Whitmore (2015),https://zenodo.org/record/3747946/files/figure.png
