 types of roost shelters. Echolocation call to search for prey is distinctive, beginning with upward sweep in frequency, then becomes steady at 48—51 kHz, and ends with downward sweep of this frequency range—all occurring for 6-8 milliseconds. In Singapore, echolocation call reportedly has a minimum frequency of 46 kHz and a maximum of 49-3 kHz.",,,Bates | rancis & Kingston (2008) | Corbet & Hill (1992) | Lekagul & McNeely (1977) | Nowak (1994) | Payne et al. (1985) | Pottie et al. (2005) | Temminck (1838),https://zenodo.org/record/3749230/files/figure.png
